Una Smith has helped hundreds of veterans and their families through her work with SSAFA Dumbarton volunteer honoured with special membership for armed forces charity - Daily Record Una Smith of Dumbarton was presented with honorary life membership of SSAFA Glasgow.
To mark this event, the award was presented by Prince Michael of Kent, president of the Soldiers’, Sailors’ and Airmen’s Families Association worldwide, when he visited the Glasgow branch of the charity.
Una said: “I have found my time at SSAFA very fulfilling and enjoyable.”
Throughout the years Una has been a volunteer with SSAFA she has helped hundreds of veterans and their families.
In addition, as head of fundraising for the branch for a number of years, she has generated thousands of pounds for this vital charity.
 